sql:
SELECT MAX(bmi) AS max_bmi
FROM participants
WHERE diabetic = 'Yes';

SELECT AVG(bmi) AS average_bmi
FROM health_survey
WHERE heart_disease = 'Yes' AND physical_health >= 7;

SELECT p.bmi, hr.physical_health
FROM participants p
INNER JOIN health_ratings hr ON p.survey_id = hr.survey_id;

external_knowledge:
- Heart disease or stroke indicate significant health issues;
- BMI between 25 and 35 represents overweight to obese categories;
- An average health rating greater than 5 implies exceeding moderate health levels.
